!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

employment /ɪmˈplɔɪmənt/

1. N-UNCOUNT Employment is the fact of having a paid job. 工作 

例： She was unable to find employment. 她没能找到工作。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Employment is the fact of employing someone. 雇用 

例： ...the employment of children under nine. …9岁以下儿童的雇用。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Employment is the work that is available in a country or area. 就业 

例： ...economic policies designed to secure full employment. …为确保充分就业而制定的经济政策。

</div>

